title: Tough lines on Ukraine and China: See the policy fallout from the U.S. election.
dc:creator: Steven Erlanger and Alexandra Stevenson

media:content.media:credit: Lynsey Addario for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: A Ukrainian woman wept upon meeting a Ukrainian soldier after Russia formally retreated from the Kherson region. Europe is trying to determine what the U.S. election results will mean for U.S. support of Ukraine.
